    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Scroll of Harm</strong> (Level 6 Necromancy)</p><p>You unleash a virulent disease on a creature that you can see within range. The target must make a constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 14d6 necrotic damage, or half as much damage on a successful save. The damage can't reduce the target's hit points below 1. If the target fails the saving throw, its hit point maximum is reduced for 1 hour by an amount equal to the necrotic damage it took. Any effect that removes a disease allows a creature's hit point maximum to return to normal before that time passes.</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V, S</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action | <strong>Range:</strong> 60 feet | <strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><em>Classes: Cleric</em></p>",
